	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-24T04:12:56">Sterling Energy plc is an upstream oil and gas company. The Company is an operator of international licenses with a focus on projects in Africa. It has exploration projects in Cameroon, Somaliland, Madagascar and Mauritania together with a production interest in Mauritania. The Company operates in the Africa segment. The Africa segment includes its exploration and development activities. Its Ntem concession lies adjacent to the southern maritime border of the Douala Basin province of Cameroon. Water depths range from around 400 meters to 2,000 meters across this around 2,319 square kilometer block. Its Odewayne is an unexplored acreage position comprising an area of around 22,840 square kilometers. Its Ampasindava block covers around 7,379 square kilometers and is located in the Majunga basin, offshore Madagascar. Water depths across block range from around 20 meters to 2,500 meters. Block C-3 is located within the Nouakchott sub-basin and covers around 9,800 square kilometers.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-07-28T23:09:38">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Sterling Energy plc revenues decreased 61% to $3.6M. Net loss totaled $1.5M vs. income of $1.7M. Revenues reflect a decrease in demand for the Company's products and services due to unfavorable market conditions. Net loss reflects Impairment reversal of oil and gas asset increase from $0K to $131K (expense), Finance income decrease of 28% to $135K (income).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
